───────────────────────────────────────────────────

Alert usage sites:

| File | Call site | Alert title |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| BasketVC.swift:221 | `book()` — empty basket | "Warning!" |
| BasketVC.swift:316 | `postNonceToServer()` — payment success | "Payment info:" |
| BasketVC.swift:337 | `postNonceToServer()` — booking failed | "Booking failed with payment info:" |
| BasketVC.swift:343 | `postNonceToServer()` — payment error | "Booking failed with payment info:" |
| MenuVC.swift:149 | `viewDidLoad` — activation required | "Warning!" via presentAlertWithFunction |
| MenuVC.swift:154 | `viewDidLoad` — session error | "No valid session!" |
| MenuVC.swift:157 | `viewDidLoad` — network error | "Error!" |
| MenuVC.swift:169 | `logoutTapped` — logout success | "Logout Successful" |
| MenuVC.swift:172 | `logoutTapped` — logout failed | "Logout Failed" |
| PurchasesVC.swift:234 | delete purchase success | "Info" |
| PurchasesVC.swift:275 | error handler | "Error" |
| SignupVC.swift:131,134,137,152,185,188,272 | various signup errors | multiple |

Alert definitions (HomeVC.swift lines 224–266):

```swift
// UIViewController extension — currently embedded in HomeVC.swift
extension UIViewController {
    func presentAlert(withTitle title: String, message: String)
    func presentAlertWithFunction(withTitle title: String, message: String, function: String)
}
```

WebSocket current state (Websocket.swift):

```swift
case .string(let text):
    print("Received: \(text)")   // ← message is dropped, no observer
case .data(let data):
    print("Received binary data: \(data)")   // ← dropped
```

───────────────────────────────────────────────────
🎯 Goals
───────────────────────────────────────────────────

Alert Controllers:
- Move alert helpers out of HomeVC.swift into a dedicated AlertPresenter.swift
- Replace magic-string function parameter with a typed Action enum
- Add SwiftUI .alert() binding pattern via AlertItem struct
- Preserve all existing call sites — no behaviour change

WebSocket Incoming Messages:
- Publish incoming string messages via Combine @Published / PassthroughSubject
- Define typed WebSocketMessage enum (seatUpdate, genericNotification, unknown)
- Parse server JSON payload into structured model
- Allow any VC or SwiftUI View to subscribe and react
- Show seat-availability alert or trigger seat map refresh on seatUpdate event

───────────────────────────────────────────────────
❗ Functional Requirements
───────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Alert Controllers

REQ-ALERT-1: Move presentAlert and presentAlertWithFunction out of HomeVC.swift
  into a new file: SwiftLoginScreen/Alerts/AlertPresenter.swift

REQ-ALERT-2: Replace the "function" string parameter with a typed enum:
  enum AlertAction {
      case none
      case resendActivation   // replaces "sendEmail"
      case custom(() -> Void)
  }

REQ-ALERT-3: New signature (backward compatible via default parameter):
  func presentAlert(withTitle title: String, message: String, action: AlertAction = .none)

REQ-ALERT-4: Provide SwiftUI-compatible AlertItem for use with .alert(item:):
  struct AlertItem: Identifiable {
      var id = UUID()
      var title: String
      var message: String
      var action: AlertAction = .none
  }

REQ-ALERT-5: All existing call sites MUST compile unchanged
  (presentAlert(withTitle:message:) signature is preserved)

REQ-ALERT-6: presentAlertWithFunction call sites in MenuVC MUST be updated
  to use the new AlertAction.resendActivation case

REQ-ALERT-7: No new third-party dependencies — use UIKit UIAlertController only

## WebSocket Incoming Messages

REQ-WS-1: WebSocketManager MUST expose a Combine publisher for incoming messages:
  var messagePublisher: AnyPublisher<WebSocketMessage, Never>

REQ-WS-2: Define WebSocketMessage enum:
  enum WebSocketMessage {
      case seatUpdate(screeningDateId: String, seats: [SeatUpdate])
      case genericNotification(text: String)
      case unknown(raw: String)
  }

REQ-WS-3: WebSocketManager.receiveMessage() MUST parse incoming JSON and
  publish a typed WebSocketMessage instead of only printing

REQ-WS-4: Expected server JSON payload format (from mbooks WebSocketServer):
  { "type": "SEAT_UPDATE", "screeningDateId": "5", "seats": [...] }
  Fall back to genericNotification for any non-JSON or unrecognised format

REQ-WS-5: SeatsVC (or its ViewModel) MUST subscribe to messagePublisher and
  refresh the seat map when a seatUpdate message arrives for the current screeningDateId

REQ-WS-6: A received seatUpdate MUST show a non-blocking toast or inline
  indicator ("Seat map updated") — NOT a modal UIAlertController
  (to avoid interrupting the user mid-selection)

REQ-WS-7: A received genericNotification SHOULD show a presentAlert with
  title "Notification" and the message text

REQ-WS-8: Reconnect logic MUST be preserved unchanged (3-second backoff)

REQ-WS-9: MUST remain compatible with URLSessionWebSocketTask (no new WS library)

───────────────────────────────────────────────────
🔗 Architecture Constraints
───────────────────────────────────────────────────

Alert:
- AlertPresenter.swift lives in SwiftLoginScreen/Alerts/ (new folder)
- UIViewController extension is the delivery mechanism for UIKit VCs
- SwiftUI views use @State var alertItem: AlertItem? + .alert(item: $alertItem)
- AppDelegate / AppServices do NOT need changes

WebSocket:
- WebSocketManager is a class (not actor) — use DispatchQueue.main for UI publishes
- Use PassthroughSubject<WebSocketMessage, Never> internally,
  expose as AnyPublisher via .eraseToAnyPublisher()
- SeatUpdate model: { seatId, seatNumber, seatRow, isReserved }
  (matches mbooks DAO.getSeatsForScreening response shape)
- WebSocketManager is held by AppDelegate / AppServices — inject into VCs
  via HasAppServices protocol (existing pattern)
- No new singleton — pass via dependency injection

